9b7ac9-920b-7530-b85a-103e52302ff8","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Will Enger","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"CascadeOC Website: https://cascadeoc.org/result/wednesday-evening-series-2-lake-wilderness-park/","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club","cumulative_event_comments":"Thank You to all our volunteers!\nDue to some confusion of the organizers, some participants did Course 3+2 instead of Course 2+3, giving two different classes.\n\nThe second event in this year’s Wednesday Evening Series! The Wednesday Evening Series is our most relaxed, casual set of navigation events, held in local parks once the weather warms up. These events are a little more low-key than those in the WIOL/Winter Series, and we always offer a barbeque afterward for all participants. Decompress after work, with or without your coworkers. Or meet your family at the park and enjoy a night off from cooking. Or meet a bunch of friends at the park for an evening of exploring together, chatting over some food, and finishing up with frisbee on the lawn.\nEvents in the Wednesday Evening Series are generally less challenging (both physically and navigationally) than many of our other events, and are therefore great for beginners and those less experienced with orienteering – while also offering a challenge to longtime participants of the sport.\nCheck back later for special notes from the Course Designer(s). Lake Wilderness Park offers a interesting mix of open parkland and forested terrain crisscrossed with trails; there will be little to no off-trail travel necessary. The park is largely flat and sits on the northern shore of Lake Wilderness, with nice views of Mount Rainier when the weather allows."}
